medical_history.history_of_present_illness: The patient first noticed the xanthelasmas 10 years earlier. Over the course of treatment with rosuvastatin, she reported some regression of the xanthelasmas within 12 months, and after 4 years of treatment, they had almost completely regressed.
medical_history.past_medical_history: Gastroesophageal reflux and a remote history of papillary thyroid cancer treated surgically. No history of dyslipidemia, coronary artery disease, or stroke.
